<includeonly>{{Category/table | category={{{#userparam|}}} | page={{{1|}}} | nested=yes }}</includeonly><noinclude>
Renders a single subobject instance as a full Category/table.

Called from Category/subobject-instances via {{#ask: | format=template | template=Category/subobject-instance | userparam=<SubCat>}}:

* {{{1}}}            - the subobject's fragment identifier (e.g. "ParentPage#_abc123")
* {{{#userparam}}} - the subobject's category name (without namespace prefix).
                       SMW's format=template uses #userparam (with hash) for the
                       userparam option passed via #ask.

Reuses Category/table so subobjects render with the exact same look as
the parent category page. `nested=yes` tells Category/table this is a
mini-table render: suppress Backlinks and subobject sections that only
make sense at the top level.
</noinclude>
